com.dev.yvgenijsharovskij.n5kanjiandkanjistoryquiz.util

Class ExpandableListHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dev.yvgenijsharovskij.n5kanjiandkanjistoryquiz.util.ExpandableListHandler

  • public class ExpandableListHandler
extends java.lang.Object
    Sets and gets the ExpandableListView group and child data for the answer and question quiz types, as well as adjusts the ExpandableListView height.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Yvgenij Sharovskij

      Constructor to set the the ExpandableListView group and child data according to the pre-sets defined in QNASettings and the user-defined input.

      • setListViewHeight

        public void setListViewHeight(android.widget.ExpandableListView listView,
                              int group)
        Manually sets the ExpandableListView height for each group, depending on whether the group is expanded.
        Note: the ExpandableListView for the QNA is declared inside a ScrollView, which means that we get a scrollable object within a scrollable view, and this is discouraged due to e.g. intercepts on touch.
        Therefore, the ExpandableListView height is adjusted during run time in ExpandableListViewPreference by calling this method.
        The ExpandableListView height is set independently of the group count.
        Parameters:
        listView - the ExpandableListView
        group - the ExpandableListView group
